reviews.text:
Good food and well prepared Suchi, maybe best in Dili.
Be aware only cash no credit cards.

I love Japanese food.  Not brave enough to try sushi here yet though. I ordered the cold ramen. You know that cucumber dish often served in Thai restaurants (in the States),  the cucumber in the dish tastes just like that (minus the chilis). If you don't like vinegar this dish isn't for you. 
I also love iced tea which I've found hard to get in Timor. Until now. The cold jasmine tea without sugar is great.
It used to be better

One of the best Japanese restaurants in dili. They have daily Bento boxes for lunch which are about 10 bucks. They have a very large menu with all types of things from Sushi, tempura, curry and much much more. The place is romantic enough for a date. It has a little cherry blossom tree and a lot of other Japanese decorations. I really like the salmon and tuna sushi rolls. They have good miso soup as well. To get a fifth star they should do three things, 1 never ever run out of green tea - this is a Japanese restaurants after all, 2 make bigger portion sizes for the edamame beans, and 3 get the mosquitoes under control. This place does not accept a credit card.

A beautiful walk up the building, but a lot of stairs so be ready for the climb! The view at the top is worth it though for a free view of Fukuoka city and to watch the planes coming in to land. Lovely, peaceful and relaxing. Bring a coffee and your set 😎👌🏼

I thought this place was architectural cool. Huge terraced building full of trees over looking the park. There is actually a winding staircase if you want to climb the building. Iinside is very modern with shops and restaurants in  the basement floors. The ground floor houses the music halls and has a large tourist information office which includes a coffee shop.
Cool for exercise and a decent view. Don't go out of your way, it's not amazing, but good
This place is a nice piece of nature in the city. It’s a bit of a climb but the views of the city from the top are superb.
Beautiful building... Every building in the world should be like this!
Best place to sakura viewing 😍 there's a lot of surprise and there is also shrine at the top
Quieter than Ohori corn. Good views. A really excellent hotdog/hamburger van.
Serene and quiet, good views of the ports, but quite a steep hill to climb to get to it! Worth the effort though.
Whole family of black kites near the burger shop. Incredible to see!
Nice walk and nice view!

Definitely a good lookout spot to Fukuoka city. Required a little hike up a small hill. Go down at Muromi station.  There are some crane nests along the walk on the tree top. Fantastic view as the reward.

This was a very beautiful shrine with a beautiful location! There are many shrines in the area but I would definitely recommend making the small hike up the hill to see this one. It has a beautiful view of the city and walking up to it takes you through a very cute Japanese neighborhood. It winds up through a more forested area of the city which is also refreshing.

The reward for climbing the hundred or more steps to the Atago Shrine is a panoramic view of the northern coastal area of Fukuoka City. Since the surrounding landscape is quite flat and there are not many distinctive landmarks apart from the iconic Fukuoka Tower to the northeast; the scene is not a spectacular one.

There is a building on the right side of the road further up from the parking lot. There is an elevator inside that goes to the top of the hill where the shrine is located.
Very nice view
Nice temple with a really excellent view over the city. The smell of incense as I walked up the steps to the shrine was great.

Really delicious ramen.  The broth was rich and beautifully seasoned.  The noodles were wheatey and toothsome (definitely get a refill).  The pork was tender, juicy, and flavorful.  Service was lightning-fast and efficient.  This place deserves 5 stars for sure.
Ichiran always does a great job maintaining its quality at an affordable price. This store has two floors, where the second floor is the usual single booths. Quite a bit of queue.
Ichiran always maintains it's quality in every chain. The service is also very nice and fast. The prices are a little more than other local stores though.

Ichiran has the best tasting ramen I've had during my trip in Japan. Though this branch doesn't taste any different to the branch in other cities, it's nice to try ramen in the head office/city where it was born.

The second floor of the restaurant provides private booth for one person whilst the first floor has tables for multiple people.
24/7 classic Ichiran ramen, no more commentary needed! (Although the scenery is very nice, staff is great as always).

This food atrium is located on the 5th floor of Hakata, Fukuoka's signature mall, Canal City. This place allows you to try signature noodles and broths from eight of Japan's regions. Waiting time is around 15-20 minutes during mealtimes, and customers order their noodles from the vending machine outside each store. These machines are available in English too, you'll receive a small rectangular ticket. The famous Tonkotsu noodles is a must-try if you are in the region.
Went to Shodai Hidechan. Reasonable value and easy introduction to Hakata ramen. Tasty ramen - English menu available.

Actually it’s so normal than I expected. It was quite tasty but it wasn’t so good neither memorable. And price is a bit expensive than normal ramen restaurant. It’s enough to visit one time. I recommend to search another ramen restaurant.
Was my first ramen in Japan and it tasted amazing!
Didn’t try it as there is Ichiran at B1. The tomatoe based ramen has the longest queue.
Nice quaint plc to hang goyza n chicken wings

The gyoza was awesome! They just melted in your mouth and had the right amount of crunch. The flavor was addictive and went well with a glass of beer. The chicken skin was also a nice surprise. The flavor was smoky, fatty, salty and vinegary. It is a great drinking snack. Overall, I would highly recommend to visit.
Food quality is good
Dumpling is perfect. but All seats are smoking place.
Excellent food, unbelievable variety of tastes.

結婚式の二次会で利用
雰囲気は悪くない

パンケーキ
2015.6月 福岡ウォーカー
